{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem is decomposed into checking the existence of a power of 2 (k(n)=1) and then investigating the next possible values for the number of set bits (k(n)=2 and k(n)=3) using modular arithmetic.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine if there exists an integer n such that 2023*n is a power of 2. If not, explain why based on the prime factorization of 2023."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Test the possibility of k(n)=2. This requires checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b for some integers a, b. Specifically, check if 2023 divides 2^m + 1 for some m. If k(n)=2 is impossible, investigate if k(n)=3 is possible."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent should take the result from helper_1 to determine if the minimum k(n) is 1. If helper_1 concludes k(n) cannot be 1, the parent should use the result from helper_2 to determine if the minimum k(n) is 2 or 3 (or higher, though the subproblem directs focus to 3)."
}

